54.1	Show_Boat	Show Boat	Show Boat is a 1927 musical in two acts, with music by Jerome Kern and book and lyrics by Oscar Hammerstein II. Based on Edna Ferber's bestselling novel of the same name, the musical follows the lives of the performers, stagehands, and dock workers on the Cotton Blossom, a Mississippi River show boat, over a span of nearly fifty years, from 1880 to 1927. Its themes include racial prejudice and tragic, enduring love. The musical contributed such classic songs as "Ol' Man River," "Make Believe," and "Can't Help Lovin' Dat Man."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/fb/Show_Boat.jpg/200px-Show_Boat.jpg
